The paper deals with scene parsing, which is a computer vision task, and proposes a novel approach using recurrent convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions that the system is trained in an end-to-end manner, which suggests that it may fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper does not rely on any segmentation methods or task-specific features, indicating that it may also belong to the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with labeling pixels in an image, which is a natural language processing task, suggesting that it may also fall under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
